This paper is primarily focused on visual recognition tasks, specifically on improving the efficiency of bilinear models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a novel method for compact pooling, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the discriminative power of bilinear pooling, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification and few-shot learning, which are tasks commonly associated with multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) categories.
